  "texts": [
    "This process allows the AI to learn a policy that will maximize the expected cumulative reward over time.",
    "The MDP consists of states, behavioral actions, a transition model, and a reward function.",
    "The model first assumes that some environment or world w exists, where an AI agent can take some behavioral action a from a set of all possible actions A, within the context of world states that are represented by s from a set of all possible states S.",
    "The R s a, then represents the immediate reward signal that the AI agent receives when taking some behavioral action a in state s and following policy π, which is called the state-value function for policy π.",
    "The expected cumulative discounted reward can then be expressed as V s"
  ],
